Postman Collection: Messaging App API Testing

BASE URL: http://localhost:8000/api/

Authentication Endpoints:
1. Get JWT Token
   - URL: /token/
   - Method: POST
   - Body: {"username": "user", "password": "pass"}

2. Refresh Token
   - URL: /token/refresh/
   - Method: POST
   - Body: {"refresh": "refresh_token"}

Conversation Endpoints:
1. List Conversations
   - URL: /conversations/
   - Method: GET
   - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>

2. Create Conversation
   - URL: /conversations/
   - Method: POST
   - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
   - Body: {"participants": [user_ids]}

Message Endpoints:
1. List Messages
   - URL: /messages/
   - Method: GET
   - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>

2. Send Message
   - URL: /messages/
   - Method: POST
   - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
   - Body: {"conversation": "uuid", "content": "message"}

Testing Scenarios:
1. Unauthorized access should return 401
2. Accessing other users' conversations should return 403
3. Valid users should be able to access their conversations
4. Pagination should return 20 messages per page
5. Filtering by conversation and timestamp should work